solution.p:
We have,

			\sin \theta = \frac{\rm opposite}{\rm hypotenuse} = \frac{\rm opposite}{7} = \frac{1}{5} \Rightarrow {\rm opposite} = 7 \times \frac{1}{5} = \frac{7}{5}

		We could now find the adjacent side using the pythagorean theorem:

			\left(\frac{7}{5}\right)^2 + \left(\rm adjacent\right)^2  = 7^2
			\Rightarrow \left(\rm adjacent\right)^2 = 49-\frac{49}{25} = \frac{1176}{25}

		Thus, the adjacent side is \sqrt{\frac{1176}{25}} = \frac{14\sqrt{6}}{5}.
